<Layout title="flip-edge — Ian Bragg">
  <h1>flip-edge</h1>
  <p class="tagline">Vision-driven marketplace valuation — Claude Vision API + Playwright pipeline that turns marketplace screenshots into structured listings and comp prices.</p>

  <div class="signals">
    <span class="signal">Status: early</span>
    <span class="signal">Python · Claude Vision · Playwright · Typer</span>
  </div>

  <h2>The thesis</h2>
  <p>
    Resale-arbitrage opportunities on local marketplaces (Facebook
    Marketplace, OfferUp, Craigslist) get burned away fast by experienced
    flippers. The remaining edge is speed: how quickly you can convert a
    listing photo into "this is a $X item, comps are $Y on the resale side,
    fair offer is $Z." Vision models close that gap dramatically.
  </p>

  <h2>What works today</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Playwright-driven scraping primitives for marketplace surfaces (login
      flows, screenshot capture, listing pagination).</li>
    <li>CLI scaffold using Typer; clean separation of <em>capture</em>,
      <em>extract</em>, <em>price</em>, <em>rank</em> phases.</li>
    <li>Secrets routed through Bitwarden CLI — same pattern as apld-edge.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What's next</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Claude Vision extraction: photo → structured listing (brand, model,
      condition, accessories, defects).</li>
    <li>Comps integration: eBay sold-listings + Mercari + Poshmark APIs to
      anchor target sell-price.</li>
    <li>Margin ranker: surface only deals above a configurable profit
      threshold.</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
